1
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:22,940
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

2
00:00:24,350 --> 00:00:28,320
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

3
00:00:30,980 --> 00:00:36,070
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

4
00:00:37,270 --> 00:00:42,180
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

5
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:46,990
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

6
00:00:46,990 --> 00:00:50,060
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

7
00:00:50,770 --> 00:00:55,720
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

8
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:59,940
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

9
00:00:59,940 --> 00:01:03,220
♪The open sky rises high♪

10
00:01:03,760 --> 00:01:08,890
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

11
00:01:09,660 --> 00:01:12,920
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

12
00:01:12,920 --> 00:01:16,280
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

13
00:01:16,690 --> 00:01:22,360
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

14
00:01:22,770 --> 00:01:26,020
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

15
00:01:26,020 --> 00:01:29,350
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

16
00:01:29,750 --> 00:01:33,790
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

17
00:01:33,790 --> 00:01:35,040
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,067 --> 00:01:37,856
=Episode 43=

19
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:40,832
(Outpatient)

20
00:01:43,136 --> 00:01:44,018
- Age?
- Eight.

21
00:01:44,864 --> 00:01:45,696
Next.

22
00:01:45,856 --> 00:01:46,688
- Second floor.
- Next.

23
00:01:47,296 --> 00:01:48,296
Which department?

24
00:01:48,696 --> 00:01:49,735
Cardiology.

25
00:01:58,696 --> 00:02:01,296
All his test results are normal,

26
00:02:01,296 --> 00:02:02,576
and his intellectual development

27
00:02:02,576 --> 00:02:04,615
has improved since the last time.

28
00:02:04,615 --> 00:02:05,535
Thank you, doctor.

29
00:02:06,576 --> 00:02:07,455
Don't thank me.

30
00:02:07,455 --> 00:02:08,536
Thank yourself.

31
00:02:09,175 --> 00:02:11,416
You've put in tremendous effort
as a mother.

32
00:02:13,775 --> 00:02:15,495
We set a date for the surgery.

33
00:02:15,495 --> 00:02:16,296
Take a look.

34
00:02:16,655 --> 00:02:17,211
Okay.

35
00:02:20,416 --> 00:02:21,215
Doctor.

36
00:02:22,935 --> 00:02:24,136
Why are the costs

37
00:02:24,895 --> 00:02:27,136
so much higher
than what you showed me last time?

38
00:02:27,136 --> 00:02:29,256
Because we're conducting
a valve replacement.

39
00:02:29,775 --> 00:02:30,696
Domestic ones

40
00:02:30,696 --> 00:02:33,775
haven't worked well
in clinical applications.

41
00:02:33,775 --> 00:02:35,935
So we have to use imported ones.

42
00:02:36,536 --> 00:02:37,935
We've got no choice.

43
00:02:37,935 --> 00:02:39,536
Then, after the surgery,

44
00:02:39,536 --> 00:02:41,016
there will be costs for the ICU.

45
00:02:41,696 --> 00:02:43,775
That estimate might be on the low side.

46
00:02:44,175 --> 00:02:44,895
So

47
00:02:45,895 --> 00:02:47,495
does this surgery time work for you?

48
00:02:49,935 --> 00:02:51,016
Shall we delay it?

49
00:02:51,856 --> 00:02:53,455
No, we'll figure something out.

50
00:02:54,096 --> 00:02:54,683
Okay.

51
00:03:14,816 --> 00:03:15,696
Qin'e.

52
00:03:17,136 --> 00:03:18,136
Yuzhi.

53
00:03:18,136 --> 00:03:19,008
Where are you going?

54
00:03:19,136 --> 00:03:20,175
We're heading home.

55
00:03:20,175 --> 00:03:21,016
Get in.

56
00:03:25,495 --> 00:03:28,055
Yuzhi, I'm so lucky I ran into you.

57
00:03:28,055 --> 00:03:29,416
It's scorching today.

58
00:03:30,175 --> 00:03:31,576
Don't be so formal with me.

59
00:03:38,395 --> 00:03:39,096
(Carboprost Suppositories)

60
00:03:39,096 --> 00:03:40,335
Don't touch Auntie's things.

61
00:03:43,655 --> 00:03:46,136
I went for a checkup today too.

62
00:03:46,976 --> 00:03:48,016
How's the kid?

63
00:03:48,615 --> 00:03:49,455
He's doing well.

64
00:03:49,895 --> 00:03:51,775
He can probably
get the surgery next month.

65
00:03:52,935 --> 00:03:54,655
You've been through a lot.

66
00:03:54,816 --> 00:03:56,775
Seeing light
at the end of the tunnel, huh?

67
00:03:57,096 --> 00:03:57,935
Almost there.

68
00:03:57,935 --> 00:03:59,256
Just one last push needed.

69
00:03:59,976 --> 00:04:02,576
Everything's going to be fine.
Don't overthink it.

70
00:04:07,455 --> 00:04:09,376
With your fame now,

71
00:04:09,376 --> 00:04:11,376
it's easy to make money.

72
00:04:12,935 --> 00:04:14,416
I only know opera.

73
00:04:16,176 --> 00:04:17,895
Did you hear something from Wei Xiaohui?

74
00:04:18,616 --> 00:04:20,576
From a filthy mouth
comes no decent speech.

75
00:04:20,576 --> 00:04:21,895
You got me wrong.

76
00:04:21,895 --> 00:04:22,696
You know what?

77
00:04:22,696 --> 00:04:23,566
Those people

78
00:04:23,566 --> 00:04:25,816
are just being sour,

79
00:04:26,176 --> 00:04:28,256
each one green with envy.

80
00:04:29,256 --> 00:04:30,335
Nowadays,

81
00:04:30,335 --> 00:04:33,016
if you want money, drop the artist act

82
00:04:33,016 --> 00:04:34,215
and the attitude.

83
00:04:34,655 --> 00:04:37,496
It all comes down to mutual agreement.

84
00:04:37,775 --> 00:04:38,496
You know,

85
00:04:38,496 --> 00:04:41,256
compared to singing
at rural weddings or funerals,

86
00:04:41,256 --> 00:04:42,895
it's just a different approach,

87
00:04:42,895 --> 00:04:44,136
different venue,

88
00:04:44,136 --> 00:04:45,496
and different audience.

89
00:04:45,496 --> 00:04:47,095
What's the real difference?

90
00:04:47,696 --> 00:04:49,616
Seriously, these people...

91
00:04:52,295 --> 00:04:53,016
What?

92
00:04:53,616 --> 00:04:55,295
Do you also look down on me?

93
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:56,095
No.

94
00:04:56,655 --> 00:04:57,936
We're just making ends meet.

95
00:04:57,936 --> 00:04:59,176
Who gets to be judgmental?

96
00:04:59,775 --> 00:05:01,376
You're absolutely right.

97
00:05:03,215 --> 00:05:04,376
I know a gig organizer.

98
00:05:04,376 --> 00:05:05,616
He's got plenty of jobs.

99
00:05:06,496 --> 00:05:08,095
If you're interested,

100
00:05:08,095 --> 00:05:09,176
I can connect you.

101
00:05:09,535 --> 00:05:11,376
Sing something like "Northwest Wind."

102
00:05:11,376 --> 00:05:12,535
No problem at all.

103
00:05:13,616 --> 00:05:14,736
Thanks, Yuzhi.

104
00:05:15,415 --> 00:05:16,975
Alright, think about it.

105
00:05:18,535 --> 00:05:19,496
Son.

106
00:05:19,496 --> 00:05:20,655
Look.

107
00:05:20,655 --> 00:05:23,576
We're ready for the cartoon.

108
00:05:25,016 --> 00:05:26,016
The last move.

109
00:05:26,816 --> 00:05:28,655
Come on, last one.

110
00:05:30,576 --> 00:05:32,016
Let's see.

111
00:05:32,936 --> 00:05:34,136
Look.

112
00:05:34,655 --> 00:05:36,095
Isn't it the cartoon?

113
00:05:36,855 --> 00:05:38,655
The Blue Mouse.

114
00:05:39,136 --> 00:05:40,975
Your favorite cartoon.

115
00:05:40,975 --> 00:05:42,376
A hug from Daddy.

116
00:05:42,975 --> 00:05:43,895
Here we go.

117
00:05:43,895 --> 00:05:44,855
Fly.

118
00:05:44,855 --> 00:05:46,095
- Put him down.
- Fun, huh?

119
00:05:46,095 --> 00:05:47,576
It's too much for his heart, okay?

120
00:05:48,455 --> 00:05:49,335
Are you okay?

121
00:05:49,895 --> 00:05:51,095
Are you feeling unwell?

122
00:05:54,496 --> 00:05:55,816
We set up the TV.

123
00:05:56,215 --> 00:05:57,775
He was excited, so I got carried away.

124
00:05:57,855 --> 00:05:59,095
You're so reckless.

125
00:05:59,975 --> 00:06:01,415
Thanks for coming today, though.

126
00:06:02,655 --> 00:06:03,376
Give me a second.

127
00:06:03,376 --> 00:06:04,056
Come on.

128
00:06:04,496 --> 00:06:05,335
What is it?

129
00:06:06,256 --> 00:06:08,176
I'm the Employee of the Month.

130
00:06:08,176 --> 00:06:10,136
You've given me money this month.

131
00:06:10,775 --> 00:06:12,696
You're working hard every day.

132
00:06:13,816 --> 00:06:15,295
I worked a lot last month.

133
00:06:15,775 --> 00:06:17,415
I don't spend much, anyway.

134
00:06:18,655 --> 00:06:19,335
Keep it

135
00:06:19,655 --> 00:06:20,775
for Liu Yi's surgery.

136
00:06:21,376 --> 00:06:22,455
Stop playing the hero.

137
00:06:23,176 --> 00:06:24,855
Besides, this isn't enough.

138
00:06:25,176 --> 00:06:26,455
The doctor said

139
00:06:26,816 --> 00:06:29,455
the surgery cost
plus all the other expenses

140
00:06:29,816 --> 00:06:31,496
is going to be six figures.

141
00:06:31,936 --> 00:06:32,775
That much?

142
00:06:40,535 --> 00:06:41,256
Alright then.

143
00:06:42,335 --> 00:06:43,775
I'll figure something out.

144
00:06:51,696 --> 00:06:53,136
Don't do anything illegal.

145
00:06:54,376 --> 00:06:55,535
What do you take me for?

146
00:06:58,256 --> 00:06:59,616
You've been performing a lot.

147
00:07:00,335 --> 00:07:01,176
Get more rest.

148
00:07:02,895 --> 00:07:03,775
You too.

149
00:07:26,011 --> 00:07:31,056
(No Stage)

150
00:07:31,056 --> 00:07:31,775
Thanks.

151
00:07:47,131 --> 00:07:48,936
(Roses, Greatest Hits)

152
00:07:48,936 --> 00:07:49,655
Feifei.

153
00:07:50,016 --> 00:07:52,095
Work hard here.

154
00:07:52,095 --> 00:07:53,855
I will definitely give you a raise.

155
00:07:54,775 --> 00:07:55,816
Who are you looking for?

156
00:07:59,256 --> 00:07:59,975
Mr. Hei?

157
00:08:00,376 --> 00:08:01,576
Aren't you Liu Hong...?

158
00:08:01,576 --> 00:08:02,736
Bing.

159
00:08:02,736 --> 00:08:03,496
Liu Hongbing.

160
00:08:04,455 --> 00:08:05,415
Why are you here?

161
00:08:06,056 --> 00:08:07,176
I run this place.

162
00:08:08,176 --> 00:08:09,936
So classy.

163
00:08:10,376 --> 00:08:12,256
What brings you here today?

164
00:08:14,256 --> 00:08:16,136
I have some bootleg tapes.

165
00:08:16,136 --> 00:08:17,256
Heavy Metal from abroad.

166
00:08:18,136 --> 00:08:19,016
Is anyone interested?

167
00:08:19,655 --> 00:08:20,535
From abroad?

168
00:08:22,415 --> 00:08:23,335
Let me ask around.

169
00:08:24,136 --> 00:08:24,855
Guys.

170
00:08:24,855 --> 00:08:27,256
We have some bootleg tapes from abroad.

171
00:08:27,256 --> 00:08:28,136
Come and see.

172
00:08:28,136 --> 00:08:29,455
Bootleg tapes. Let's go.

173
00:08:29,455 --> 00:08:30,335
- Go.
- Let's see.

174
00:08:34,216 --> 00:08:34,976
Feifei.

175
00:08:34,976 --> 00:08:36,856
Heavy Metal from abroad.

176
00:08:37,175 --> 00:08:37,856
You name it.

177
00:08:38,935 --> 00:08:40,136
- Let's see.
- Nirvana.

178
00:08:40,456 --> 00:08:41,096
Not bad.

179
00:08:41,096 --> 00:08:41,736
Pink Floyd.

180
00:08:41,736 --> 00:08:42,535
Any Van Halen?

181
00:08:42,535 --> 00:08:43,496
The Smashing Pumpkins?

182
00:08:43,496 --> 00:08:44,496
One by one.

183
00:08:44,496 --> 00:08:45,456
Slow down.

184
00:08:45,456 --> 00:08:46,136
Buddy.

185
00:08:46,136 --> 00:08:47,136
Get me a pen.

186
00:08:47,136 --> 00:08:48,415
Hurry, get a pen and paper.

187
00:08:48,415 --> 00:08:49,496
Let me write this down.

188
00:08:49,496 --> 00:08:50,176
How much is it?

189
00:08:50,176 --> 00:08:50,856
Fifteen each.

190
00:09:05,775 --> 00:09:06,616
This one.

191
00:09:10,655 --> 00:09:11,415
Sir.

192
00:09:11,616 --> 00:09:12,187
Bro.

193
00:09:13,336 --> 00:09:14,055
Who is this?

194
00:09:14,655 --> 00:09:15,736
Easy. He's one of us.

195
00:09:23,535 --> 00:09:24,415
Mind your head.

196
00:09:26,136 --> 00:09:26,815
Alright.

197
00:09:38,616 --> 00:09:39,895
Rock music here.

198
00:09:40,216 --> 00:09:41,216
Classical over there.

199
00:09:42,136 --> 00:09:43,895
Those are the only two types.

200
00:09:44,216 --> 00:09:45,616
They are all imported.

201
00:09:45,856 --> 00:09:47,295
I sell whatever they import.

202
00:09:49,096 --> 00:09:50,895
These are very hard to pick.

203
00:09:51,415 --> 00:09:52,935
They are all sold in bulk.

204
00:09:52,935 --> 00:09:53,935
Listen up.

205
00:09:53,935 --> 00:09:55,415
This is all we have now.

206
00:09:56,175 --> 00:09:57,935
It's hard to say when we'll have more.

207
00:10:02,695 --> 00:10:03,392
I want them all.

208
00:10:04,216 --> 00:10:04,895
Two thousand.

209
00:10:13,496 --> 00:10:14,415
Why are you here again?

210
00:10:15,336 --> 00:10:16,496
Uncle, you're back.

211
00:10:16,496 --> 00:10:17,496
Go inside.

212
00:10:17,496 --> 00:10:18,272
I'm making noodles.

213
00:10:19,935 --> 00:10:20,815
Peeled the garlic?

214
00:10:21,496 --> 00:10:22,415
I'll help you.

215
00:10:24,655 --> 00:10:26,055
Don't you have things to do?

216
00:10:26,456 --> 00:10:28,256
Why are you idling around here?

217
00:10:28,895 --> 00:10:30,815
Qin'e is busy singing opera.

218
00:10:30,815 --> 00:10:31,856
Aunt Hua isn't here.

219
00:10:32,175 --> 00:10:33,535
Someone has to look after you.

220
00:10:34,395 --> 00:10:34,976
Here.

221
00:10:38,415 --> 00:10:39,136
How is it?

222
00:10:41,055 --> 00:10:41,856
Amazing noodles.

223
00:10:43,616 --> 00:10:44,736
I'm asking about you.

224
00:10:45,376 --> 00:10:46,256
I'm doing great.

225
00:10:46,895 --> 00:10:48,856
I roam around and earn money.

226
00:10:48,856 --> 00:10:49,535
Isn't that great?

227
00:10:50,336 --> 00:10:52,856
Is the taxi company still hiring?

228
00:10:54,096 --> 00:10:55,175
Who wants to go there?

229
00:10:55,175 --> 00:10:55,856
Me.

230
00:10:56,535 --> 00:10:57,256
You?

231
00:10:58,535 --> 00:10:59,815
Stop joking around.

232
00:11:00,175 --> 00:11:01,256
You might work a pedicab.

233
00:11:01,256 --> 00:11:03,376
Cars require a driver's license.

234
00:11:03,376 --> 00:11:04,856
I can learn to drive.

235
00:11:04,856 --> 00:11:05,695
You'll teach me.

236
00:11:05,695 --> 00:11:06,935
What's so hard about it?

237
00:11:08,175 --> 00:11:10,295
Come on, stop kidding.

238
00:11:10,295 --> 00:11:11,055
I'm serious.

239
00:11:12,616 --> 00:11:14,096
The treatment costs over 100,000.

240
00:11:15,456 --> 00:11:16,695
When will you and Qin'e

241
00:11:17,295 --> 00:11:18,175
save up enough?

242
00:11:18,655 --> 00:11:20,535
Don't worry, I've got a plan.

243
00:11:22,376 --> 00:11:24,815
We can't do anything illegal.

244
00:11:24,856 --> 00:11:26,256
We've got principles.

245
00:11:26,256 --> 00:11:27,815
What are you worried about?

246
00:11:27,815 --> 00:11:28,775
Besides,

247
00:11:28,775 --> 00:11:30,256
Cungen follows me everywhere.

248
00:11:30,256 --> 00:11:31,775
How am I going to break any laws?

249
00:11:33,295 --> 00:11:34,368
When will you two remarry?

250
00:11:38,336 --> 00:11:40,016
It doesn't change anything.

251
00:11:40,655 --> 00:11:42,456
I'm taking care of everything at home.

252
00:11:42,775 --> 00:11:44,256
You've got a big heart.

253
00:11:44,496 --> 00:11:45,535
You married a wife

254
00:11:46,616 --> 00:11:48,535
and only wished to take care of her.

255
00:11:49,415 --> 00:11:51,415
Seeing them happy makes me happy.

256
00:11:52,456 --> 00:11:53,655
If you decide to

257
00:11:54,096 --> 00:11:55,736
run a small business,

258
00:11:55,736 --> 00:11:57,055
count me in.

259
00:11:57,736 --> 00:11:59,976
I can't afford to hire you.

260
00:12:01,175 --> 00:12:01,895
Why don't you

261
00:12:01,895 --> 00:12:04,055
join those provincial troupe performers?

262
00:12:29,655 --> 00:12:30,935
♪Old brother♪

263
00:12:30,935 --> 00:12:35,535
♪Let him kneel there♪

264
00:12:37,456 --> 00:12:39,856
♪After all those pleas from Xue Bao♪

265
00:12:39,856 --> 00:12:41,895
♪I can't stop mulling it over♪

266
00:12:41,895 --> 00:12:44,456
♪I'd rather give up
on this worthless brat♪

267
00:12:44,456 --> 00:12:47,216
♪But the neighbors
would call me a heartless stepmother♪

268
00:12:47,216 --> 00:12:51,415
♪Forget it, for my late husband's sake♪

269
00:12:51,415 --> 00:12:52,055
What's up?

270
00:12:54,256 --> 00:12:55,256
What are you doing?

271
00:12:56,256 --> 00:12:57,415
Why are you startled?

272
00:12:57,415 --> 00:12:59,736
You almost scared me to death.

273
00:13:00,055 --> 00:13:01,216
You made no sound at all.

274
00:13:01,216 --> 00:13:03,256
I thought you were a thief.

275
00:13:03,256 --> 00:13:05,935
What's worth stealing
in this rundown troupe?

276
00:13:06,175 --> 00:13:08,055
Scared of thieves?

277
00:13:09,336 --> 00:13:10,055
Why are you

278
00:13:10,055 --> 00:13:11,295
wearing a woman's costume?

279
00:13:11,295 --> 00:13:12,815
I switched to Laodan last year.

280
00:13:13,535 --> 00:13:18,575
Laodan roles suit me better
than Xiaosheng roles.

281
00:13:19,415 --> 00:13:21,055
Alright, whatever you think.

282
00:13:22,016 --> 00:13:23,216
Why are you rehearsing here?

283
00:13:23,336 --> 00:13:24,535
The Rehearsal Hall

284
00:13:24,535 --> 00:13:26,175
is leaking like a bathhouse.

285
00:13:26,175 --> 00:13:27,815
We can't practice there, you know?

286
00:13:27,815 --> 00:13:29,096
We have no money for repairs.

287
00:13:29,695 --> 00:13:30,736
What about the others?

288
00:13:31,376 --> 00:13:32,096
The Troupe Leader?

289
00:13:33,575 --> 00:13:34,616
Come closer.

290
00:13:35,535 --> 00:13:36,976
I'd rather keep some distance.

291
00:13:37,736 --> 00:13:38,895
I have no idea.

292
00:13:38,895 --> 00:13:39,775
You rascal...

293
00:13:40,976 --> 00:13:43,976
♪I'd rather give up
on this worthless brat♪

294
00:13:43,976 --> 00:13:47,016
♪But the neighbors
would call me a heartless stepmother♪

295
00:13:47,016 --> 00:13:51,415
♪Forget it, for my late husband's sake♪

296
00:13:51,655 --> 00:13:53,175
(Chang'an Department Store)
Dear audience.

297
00:13:53,295 --> 00:13:55,096
Good afternoon.

298
00:13:55,856 --> 00:13:57,815
A beautiful song for everyone.

299
00:13:58,055 --> 00:13:59,336
Hope you enjoy it.

300
00:13:59,456 --> 00:14:00,935
Come on, wave your hands.

301
00:14:03,016 --> 00:14:05,096
One, two, three, four.

302
00:14:10,535 --> 00:14:12,016
Hands above your heads.

303
00:14:12,016 --> 00:14:13,895
One, two, three, four.

304
00:14:17,055 --> 00:14:18,655
Come on.

305
00:14:18,655 --> 00:14:20,935
Raise your hands and dance.

306
00:14:23,016 --> 00:14:24,775
One, two, three, four.

307
00:14:26,775 --> 00:14:29,535
You over there, raise your hands.

308
00:14:42,376 --> 00:14:43,175
What are you doing?

309
00:14:44,456 --> 00:14:45,616
I got a gig here.

310
00:14:46,976 --> 00:14:48,575
I'm asking what you're doing.

311
00:14:48,575 --> 00:14:49,376
I'll sing opera.

312
00:14:50,736 --> 00:14:51,856
What are you wearing?

313
00:14:52,216 --> 00:14:53,336
You'll perform in that?

314
00:14:54,096 --> 00:14:55,256
What are you performing?

315
00:14:55,256 --> 00:14:56,136
"Northwest Wind"?

316
00:14:57,016 --> 00:14:59,055
It's harvest season. No opera bookings.

317
00:15:00,055 --> 00:15:02,535
We can't just sit around and starve.

318
00:15:02,535 --> 00:15:03,775
Have some standards.

319
00:15:04,216 --> 00:15:05,376
I won't allow this.

320
00:15:05,775 --> 00:15:07,415
We have an agreement with our client.

321
00:15:07,736 --> 00:15:09,655
You're ruining the craft, you know?

322
00:15:10,976 --> 00:15:12,376
You're disgracing Qinqiang opera.

323
00:15:12,376 --> 00:15:14,055
Have you no respect for anything?

324
00:15:14,935 --> 00:15:15,575
Uncle.

325
00:15:16,415 --> 00:15:18,695
You brought me into this opera world,
and I made it.

326
00:15:19,216 --> 00:15:20,935
But the business is declining.

327
00:15:21,736 --> 00:15:23,216
I'm not disgracing Qinqiang opera.

328
00:15:24,096 --> 00:15:25,096
It has failed me.

329
00:15:32,295 --> 00:15:33,815
I owe it all to everyone's support.

330
00:15:34,695 --> 00:15:36,256
But I'm not just a performer.

331
00:15:36,256 --> 00:15:38,240
I'm also the deputy leader
of the Youth Troupe.

332
00:15:39,376 --> 00:15:40,616
Dozens of people rely on me

333
00:15:41,256 --> 00:15:42,376
for their livelihoods.

334
00:15:45,376 --> 00:15:46,856
I'm doing this not just for Liu Yi,

335
00:15:47,535 --> 00:15:48,616
but for everyone.

336
00:15:58,175 --> 00:16:00,055
(Hu Sanyuan scolded Yi Qin'e)

337
00:16:00,096 --> 00:16:01,616
(for putting on a "monkey show")

338
00:16:01,616 --> 00:16:04,016
(and disgracing the founders
of Qinqiang opera.)

339
00:16:04,456 --> 00:16:05,496
(But at that point,)

340
00:16:05,496 --> 00:16:08,695
(even if those founders
really came to settle scores with her,)

341
00:16:09,175 --> 00:16:13,256
(she'd just drag them onstage
to perform with her.)

342
00:16:29,575 --> 00:16:32,016
Why isn't Feng Xiaoxiao back yet?

343
00:16:32,016 --> 00:16:35,096
He got promoted
from stunt double to action director.

344
00:16:35,456 --> 00:16:36,175
He's swamped.

345
00:16:36,175 --> 00:16:37,456
Many known directors want him.

346
00:16:38,216 --> 00:16:39,856
Mom, the food's getting cold.

347
00:16:39,856 --> 00:16:40,456
Eat first.

348
00:16:40,456 --> 00:16:41,935
Don't you have a flight to catch?

349
00:16:43,415 --> 00:16:46,136
Back home, you couldn't even
cook noodles properly.

350
00:16:46,935 --> 00:16:48,175
Now you can make dishes.

351
00:16:50,295 --> 00:16:52,016
I just quit my job recently,

352
00:16:52,016 --> 00:16:53,496
planning to find something new.

353
00:16:53,496 --> 00:16:55,976
Till then, I'll manage household stuff.

354
00:16:55,976 --> 00:16:57,976
It'll be useful once I get married.

355
00:16:59,376 --> 00:17:00,535
Mom, eat up.

356
00:17:00,535 --> 00:17:01,535
The food's getting cold.

357
00:17:01,535 --> 00:17:02,535
I'll join you soon.

358
00:17:04,176 --> 00:17:05,775
If he truly wanted to marry you,

359
00:17:06,375 --> 00:17:07,775
